      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_011",
      "text": "The Alchemist (book) reminds her to stay hopeful even when NEET PG prep feels overwhelming",
      "tone": "hopeful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-04",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-04",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_012",
      "text": "*aamhi pan kahi asa karu shakto* — we can do this (Marathi affirmation) sustains her during exam stress",
      "tone": "hopeful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-04",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-04",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_013",
      "text": "Marathi short stories from Anvikraman (book) help her relax after long study sessions",
      "tone": "content",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-04",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-04",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_014",
      "text": "Shivaji Park (story) reminds her to pause and find small joys during stress",
      "tone": "grateful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-04",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-04",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_015",
      "text": "Each time I read it, The Alchemist (book) reveals something new — it grows with me",
      "tone": "grateful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-05",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-05",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_016",
      "text": "the family's struggle with consent and science in The Immortal Life of Henrietta Lacks (book) moves me and teaches me about ethics",
      "tone": "grateful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-05",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-05",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_017",
      "text": "I'm seeking books like The Brothers Karamazov (book) — complex, philosophical, but finishable",
      "tone": "hopeful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-05",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-05",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_018",
      "text": "Aajcha din thoda achha lagala — finally understood beta-blockers vs CCBs, and it felt good",
      "tone": "hopeful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-06",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-06",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_019",
      "text": "I made a comparison table and explained concepts aloud like teaching myself — and that created real confidence that I actually understood",
      "tone": "proud",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-06",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-06",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_020",
      "text": "Even when new topics feel like mountains, breaking into small steps makes them manageable",
      "tone": "hopeful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-06",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-06",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_021",
      "text": "I feel like I'll never be ready for NEET PG (exam) papers",
      "tone": "anxious",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-07",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-07",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_022",
      "text": "opening revision notes when exhausted feels like an impossible struggle, but 10 mins is a trick to start",
      "tone": "hopeful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-07",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-07",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_023",
      "text": "bed becomes a trap during revision season — getting up feels like the biggest hurdle, harder than studying itself",
      "tone": "frustrated",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-07",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-07",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_024",
      "text": "receptors and drug mechanisms feel like trying to memorise a dance I can't see",
      "tone": "frustrated",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-08",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-08",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_025",
      "text": "Made a funny Krebs cycle song in Marathi folk tune with hand gestures — brother laughed and choked on his tea, and it actually stuck perfectly",
      "tone": "proud",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-08",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-08",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_026",
      "text": "Silly study songs and raps seem cheesy, but they actually work and make learning feel less intimidating",
      "tone": "hopeful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-08",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-08",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_027",
      "text": "Small affirmation stickies like 'Breathe, small steps matter' and 'Pause, you're doing well' ground me and start each day with calm and self-kindness",
      "tone": "grateful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-09",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-09",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_028",
      "text": "The kitchen is where my mind wanders to study schedules but in a calm kind of chaos — cooking softens anxious thoughts",
      "tone": "content",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-09",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-09",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_029",
      "text": "In mock tests, when I manage time and stay calm even when stuck, I feel the rhythm clicking — I'm learning that progress matters more than being perfect",
      "tone": "proud",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-09",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-09",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_030",
      "text": "My ritual after studying hard is chai, writing down what went well, and a star in my planner — it's self-celebration and reminds me small wins count",
      "tone": "grateful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-09",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-09",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_031",
      "text": "Playing harmonium for a few minutes settles my mind and helps me stay calm — music is my anchor during stressful moments",
      "tone": "content",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-09",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-09",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_032",
      "text": "understanding cooking science matters as much as executing recipes correctly",
      "tone": "hopeful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-10",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-10",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_033",
      "text": "being bold in the kitchen with garam masala feels right, even if others think it's strange",
      "tone": "proud",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-10",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-10",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_034",
      "text": "biryani feels like a kitchen exam — big, exciting, and worth documenting to learn",
      "tone": "excited",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-10",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-10",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_035",
      "text": "small steps and testing (marination first, small taste before commitment) make big scary projects feel manageable",
      "tone": "hopeful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-10",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-10",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_036",
      "text": "learning through nani's recipes and aunt's techniques connects cooking to family and culture",
      "tone": "grateful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-10",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-10",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_037",
      "text": "scrolling on my phone during study breaks makes me feel guilty and worse",
      "tone": "anxious",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-11",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-11",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_038",
      "text": "I baked cookies, trying something new beyond my usual Indian cooking (activity)",
      "tone": "excited",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-13",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-13",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_039",
      "text": "My friends love my chicken curry with coconut milk and garam masala (dish)",
      "tone": "proud",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-13",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-13",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_040",
      "text": "I'm a bit of a spice enthusiast",
      "tone": "proud",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-13",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-13",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_041",
      "text": "The way warm spices blend with coconut in cooking feels like magic",
      "tone": "content",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-13",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-13",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_042",
      "text": "Cooking teaches me that mistakes are learning moments, just like in studying — it gives me confidence that helps with exam stress",
      "tone": "hopeful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-13",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-13",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_043",
      "text": "NEET PG prep is like a storm — studies feel chaotic right now",
      "tone": "anxious",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-15",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-15",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_044",
      "text": "I measured cumin carefully (1/2 tsp instead of guessing 1 tsp) and the taste improved — precision matters in cooking just like in study",
      "tone": "proud",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-15",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-15",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_045",
      "text": "When I slow down and take one step at a time — breathing, recipe step by step, one spice, one topic — things work out, even when stressed",
      "tone": "hopeful",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-15",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-15",
      "mentions": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "mo_046",
      "text": "I'm tired after focused effort and need rest — accepting rest as part of the rhythm, not failure",
      "tone": "content",
      "sensitive": false,
      "first_seen": "2026-05-15",
      "last_seen": "2026-05-15",
      "mentions": 1
    }
